column35: Honestly, we like to take guests to Rudy's for quick and easy BBQ. Sure, its not the best but for out of towners it is and it's a good opener...then later we take them to Black's in Lockhart. And if we're coming from the airport on the first day and they're hungry, Pappasitos and Pappadeaux are always up front impressive. And Chuys....because consistency and funky atmosphere. And for some reason, everyone who talks to someone on the plane says, "OMG someone told me I have to go to Salt Lick!" so if we can't steer them from away from that, we go there too, but that is definitely not our first choice for bbq. And if we're feeling swanky, we may do Bartlett's. Between you and me, one of my new favs is La Concina De Consuelo in Rosedale which I found via Yelp. But it's a small place damnit, so don't tell anyone! ;)
